<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Connection Speed &amp; PvP</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Nick of Nudia">Nick of Nudia</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:06 p.m. 29/3/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Connection Speed &amp; PvP<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>Recently I got a rockin connection to the net. I was surprised to find out just how much difference it makes in UO. Yeah, I still play it and most anyone on Atlantic (thats all of CC, most of the mercs, and part of the Pluggers when I was playing my looting char- though I do remember getting lucky and killing Kremlin once) who has ever PK'd has killed me once or twice or more. Heh, if yer feeling sporty come to Abyss and let me get even will ya? I'm third house down from Black castle.

<P>Anyways, the question is this. How much of an advantage does a fast connect have in EQ over a slow connect? Can you outrun someone? Can you click on them or monsters first? Do you get less, "your not close enough" messages? Has anyone played it enough on varied connection to notice a difference? I heard that melee combat sucks. Does a fast connect give a melee fighter the edge he needs?
<P>Thinks about EQ but knows for sure he's in early AC beta so might just pass it up....
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
